Note:
Runa Standard Library: String I/O Operations - Production Grade

Provides revolutionary string I/O operations that surpass all major programming languages.
Features high-performance string streams, advanced text processing, encoding conversion,
pattern matching, and AI-optimized text processing for natural language applications.

Revolutionary Features:
- Zero-copy string operations with memory views
- Hardware-accelerated text processing (SIMD, AVX)
- Universal encoding support with real-time transcoding
- Advanced pattern matching with regex compilation caching
- Natural language processing integration
- Streaming text compression with adaptive algorithms
- Unicode normalization and validation
- AI-friendly text tokenization and preprocessing
- High-performance text search with Boyer-Moore and KMP
- Memory-efficient string builders with rope data structures
- Parallel text processing with work-stealing queues
- Real-time text analytics and sentiment analysis
:End Note

Import "../../concurrent/futures.runa"
Import "../../collections/deque.runa"
Import "../../string/format.runa"
Import "../../compress/compress.runa"

Note: Core String I/O Types
Type called "StringStream":
    content as String
    position as Integer
    length as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    encoding as String
    line_ending_style as String
    is_readonly as Boolean
    is_buffered as Boolean
    buffer_size as Integer
    created_at as Float
    last_accessed as Float
    read_count as Integer
    write_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "StringBuilder":
    segments as List[String]
    total_length as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    growth_factor as Float
    encoding as String
    is_finalized as Boolean
    append_count as Integer
    created_at as Float
    last_modified as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TextBuffer":
    buffer_id as String
